[2m─── src/state/prs_integration_tests.rs:0-0 ───[0m
[94m[performance · low][0m Performance: this merge-success path now clones the entire PR list
(`items().to_vec()`), mutates the clone, and replaces the whole collection via `replace_items(prs)`.
The old code updated the matched PR in-place with `iter_mut()`.

If the PR list is large, this adds an unnecessary full allocation on every successful merge. If
`replace_items` triggers a full UI redraw, it also broadens the invalidation scope beyond just the
merged PR.

Consider whether `replace_items` offers an in-place mutation path, a mutable borrow API, or can be
scoped to the changed item to keep this hot path allocation-free.



